title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a Wayang Plan that based on tenancy types with housing_tenancy = 1 finds the total number of move outs for 2024 for each tenancy type. Beside the total number for each tenancy, also the tenancy type description should be a part of the result. You don't need any sortering or ordering. Output in a textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT tenancy_types_id, move_out_year, sum_of_move_outs FROM factmoveouts) as X

operations.udf: (a: (Int, Int, Int), b: (Int, Int, Int)) => (a._1, a._3 + b._3)

operations.table: (SELECT tenancy_types_id, tenancy_description, housing_tenancy FROM tenancy_type) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val desc = r.getField(1).toString; (id, desc) }
(t: ((Int, Int), (Int, String))) => { val total = t._1._2; val desc = t._2._2; (desc, total) }

log.thoughts: Plan reads move-out data, filters for 2024, aggregates totals by tenancy type, joins with tenancy_type to attach description for housing_tenancy = 1, and outputs the (description, total) per tenancy type to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT tenancy_types_id, move_out_year, sum_of_move_outs FROM (SELECT tenancy_types_id, move_out_year, sum_of_move_outs FROM factmoveouts) as X) as X

data.udf: (a: (Int, Int, Int), b: (Int, Int, Int)) => (a._1, a._3 + b._3)

data.table: (SELECT tenancy_types_id, tenancy_description, housing_tenancy FROM (SELECT tenancy_types_id, tenancy_description, housing_tenancy FROM tenancy_type) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val desc = r.getField(1).toString; (id, desc) }
(t: ((Int, Int), (Int, String))) => { val total = t._1._2; val desc = t._2._2; (desc, total) }
